description: The Victorian Government has proposed sweeping changes to Victorian parks include fine for walking off trails, swimming in waterways and conducting research.

title: King Charles III will keep the Queen's Private Secretary in his post
description: Known in Palace corridors as a 'hatchet man' for his ability to deliver bad news, particularly relating to job cuts, it is thought that Sir Edward Young's skills will come in handy.

title: Covid heroes and Iraq war veterans to join world leaders in the procession for the Queen's funeral
description: NHS medics, emergency responders and troops honoured for their service and bravery will lead a procession after the funeral service as the Queen's coffin is taken on a final tour of the capital.

title: Her final journey ends in a haunting silence
description: With military precision, Pipe Major Paul Burns, from the Royal Regiment of Scotland, will then slowly walk away from the gothic Chapel.

title: The day that will never be forgotten
description: An estimated million people will line the streets of London to witness scenes of breathtaking pomp and splendour, punctuated by historic moments of sorrow and solemnity.

title: Alameddine member and Ay Huncho friend Murat Galasi died in Turkey
description: Member of Sydney's Alameddine crime network Murat Galasi, 33, died of heart attack while working out in Istanbul on the weekend. His rapper friend Ay Huncho posted a tribute on Saturday.

title: War veteran, 96, who saw George V lying in state in 1936, among last mourners in accessible queue
description: Veteran and wheelchair user Frank Wells, who was born six days before the Queen in April 1926, travelled from his home in Worthing, West Sussex, to Westminster Hall to pay his respects.

title: Twitter users slam Holly Willoughby and Phillip Schofield for using VIP lane to view Queen's coffin
description: The presenters of ITV daytime show This Morning were seen on the camera feed on Friday morning after using press accreditation to skip the hours-long queue  to enter Westminster Hall.

title: Queen's coffin will be retrieved to rebury later with Prince Philip and her parents
description: The Queen's coffin will be retrieved after it is lowered into St George's Chapel's Royal Vault so that it can be reburied later with Prince Philip and her parents in King George VI Memorial Chapel.

title: King Charles III plans to turn the Queen's beloved Balmoral into a museum in honour of his mother
description: The private Scottish castle which was so beloved by the Queen would be 'opened up to the public' and is likely to carry an exhibition paying tribute to her extraordinary reign.

title: Anger as New York Times links PM Liz Truss to Enoch Powell's racism
description: Under the headline 'Britain's New Prime Minister Is Still In Thrall To The Empire', the article claims Ms Truss's 'most apt antecedent' is the former Tory Minister who became an outcast.

title: Harry and Meghan's children Archie, 3, and 15-month-old Lilibet were left at home in America
description: While the Duke and Duchess of Sussex have been at the vigil in Westminster Hall this week, Archie, 3 and 15-month-old Lilibet are believed to have remained behind in America.

title: Cost of living: Low income couples could get £2,500 boost in emergency Budget this Friday
description: A plan in Kwasi Kwarteng's budget would allow the transfer of all personal tax allowances between married couples and civil partners when one earns less than £12,570.

title: Mail on Sunday Comment: The best way we can honour the Queen is to emulate her
description: MAIL ON SUNDAY: Tomorrow the long, sad days bring us to the edge of the tomb, to the last lament and to the chilly beginning of a new era, whose nature we cannot know.

title: Facebook: Breastfeeding clothing firm has lost thousands after being hit by no-nudity rule
description: A British firm selling clothes that make breastfeeding easier has lost thousands after its Facebook adverts were banned for breaching adult content policies.

title: Queen's funeral could ECLIPSE 32 million who watched Westminster Abbey service for Diana
description: Television experts predict UK that viewing figures for tomorrow's funeral may eclipse the 32 million who watched the Westminster Abbey service for Diana, Princess of Wales.

title: Horse racing: Men willing to bet on horses after weighing up the runners' chances have higher IQ
description: Betting on horse-racing may not be such a mug's game after all - a study found that men who are willing to risk cash after weighing up the runners' chances have a higher IQ than those who do not.

title: 'Queue views' study finds most people paying respects to the Queen want to show gratitude over grief
description: The first academic 'queue views' study, led by Professor Rob Johns of Essex University, has revealed most people paying respects to the Queen want to show gratitude rather than grief.

title: Princes Andrew, Harry and Princess Beatrice could lose 'stand-in status'
description: Princes Andrew, Harry and Princess Beatrice could lose their 'stand-in status' if King Charles makes counsellors working members of the Royal family.

title: Axe-wielding man goes berserk inside McDonald's in crime-ridden NYC, waving blade at customers
description: Video on social media shows an axe-wielding man going on a rampage inside a McDonald's on Delancey Street on the Lower East Side. Michael Palacios, 31, was charged with criminal mischief.

title: This Morning bosses deny Holly Willoughby and Phillip Schofield had 'VIP access' to Queen's coffin
description: This Morning bosses have denied Holly Willoughby and Phillip Schofield had 'VIP access' and filed 'past the Queen lying in state' as they filmed a segment for the programme.
